idn't<br />want to do the full version check.<br /><br />We already know there were *some* crc's (we checked that at the top of<br />check_version(), but we've also checked it in "same_magic()" - it's<br />what makes us ignore the exact version number), but this particular<br />symbol doesn't have a crc. Just let it through, because we have bugs<br />in binutils.<br /><br />So your extra complexity logic seems actively wrong. It makes<br />MODVERSIONS not work at all, rather than limp along. You're better off<br />just not having MODVERSIONS.<br /><br />               Linus<br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
